  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I gain weight if I'm 5'11 and 119 pounds?",
  "response": "Gaining weight in a healthy and sustainable way involves increasing your calorie intake, eating nutrient-dense foods, and incorporating strength training to build muscle. At 5'11 and 119 pounds, you are underweight, so it\u2019s important to focus on gaining weight in a way that improves your overall health. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Calculate Your Calorie Needs**\n   - First, determine your **basal metabolic rate (BMR)**, which is the number of calories your body needs at rest. You can use an online BMR calculator.\n   - Add 300\u2013500 calories to your daily intake for steady weight gain. For faster weight gain, increase by 500\u2013700 calories.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Eat Calorie-Dense, Nutrient-Rich Foods**\n   Focus on foods that are high in calories but also provide essential nutrients:\n   - **Proteins:** Eggs, chicken, fish, lean beef, tofu, beans, lentils, Greek yogurt, and protein shakes.\n   - **Carbohydrates:** Whole grains (brown rice, quinoa, oats), potatoes, sweet potatoes, pasta, and bread.\n   - **Healthy Fats:** Avocados, nuts, seeds, nut butter, olive oil, and fatty fish like salmon.\n   - **Dairy:** Whole milk, cheese, and yogurt.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Increase Meal Frequency**\n   - Eat 5\u20136 smaller meals throughout the day instead of 3 large ones.\n   - Add snacks between meals, such as trail mix, protein bars, or smoothies.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Drink Your Calories**\n   - Consume calorie-rich beverages like smoothies, shakes, or homemade weight-gain drinks (e.g., milk, bananas, peanut butter, oats, and protein powder).\n   - Avoid filling up on low-calorie drinks like water, tea, or diet soda before meals.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Incorporate Strength Training**\n   - Focus on resistance training (weights, bodyweight exercises) to build muscle rather than just gaining fat.\n   - Target major muscle groups and progressively increase the intensity of your workouts.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Track Your Progress**\n   - Weigh yourself weekly to monitor your progress.\n   - Adjust your calorie intake if you\u2019re not gaining weight consistently (e.g., add 100\u2013200 more calories per day).\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Be Consistent and Patient**\n   - Gaining weight takes time, so stay consistent with your diet and exercise routine.\n   - Avoid unhealthy, processed foods to ensure you\u2019re gaining weight in a healthy way.\n\n---\n\n### Sample Daily Meal Plan for Weight Gain:\n**Breakfast:** Oatmeal with whole milk, banana, and almond butter.  \n**Snack:** Greek yogurt with honey and granola.  \n**Lunch:** Grilled chicken, quinoa, and avocado with a side of roasted sweet potatoes.  \n**Snack:** Smoothie with milk, protein powder, peanut butter, and oats.  \n**Dinner:** Salmon, brown rice, and steamed vegetables with olive oil.  \n**Before Bed:** Cottage cheese with mixed nuts and a piece of fruit.\n\n---\n\n### When to See a Doctor:\nIf you\u2019re struggling to gain weight despite these efforts, consult a healthcare professional to rule out underlying conditions like hyperthyroidism, food intolerances, or malabsorption issues.\n\nBy following these steps, you can achieve a healthy weight and improve your overall well-being.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
